cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.CR, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper is primarily concerned with defending deep learning models against adversarial attacks, which is a topic that falls under the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), and cryptography and security (cs.CR). The paper also proposes a new method for detecting adversarial attacks, which involves optimizing the margin between class clusters in the embedding space, which could be considered a form of optimization or search algorithm (cs.AI) or a neural network architecture (cs.NE).
